# Normal Mode (Command Mode)
[neovim] h: Move cursor left (normal mode)
[neovim] j: Move cursor down (normal mode)
[neovim] k: Move cursor up (normal mode)
[neovim] l: Move cursor right (normal mode)
[neovim] w: Move cursor to start of next word (normal mode)
[neovim] b: Move cursor to start of previous word (normal mode)
[neovim] e: Move cursor to end of next word (normal mode)
[neovim] 0: Move cursor to beginning of line (normal mode)
[neovim] $: Move cursor to end of line (normal mode)
[neovim] gg: Go to top of file (normal mode)
[neovim] G: Go to bottom of file (normal mode)
[neovim] Ctrl+f: Page down (normal mode)
[neovim] Ctrl+b: Page up (normal mode)
[neovim] zz: Center current line on screen (normal mode)
[neovim] H: Move cursor to top of screen (normal mode)
[neovim] M: Move cursor to middle of screen (normal mode)
[neovim] L: Move cursor to bottom of screen (normal mode)
[neovim] dd: Delete current line (normal mode)
[neovim] yy: Yank (copy) current line (normal mode)
[neovim] p: Paste after cursor (normal mode)
[neovim] P: Paste before cursor (normal mode)
[neovim] x: Delete character under cursor (normal mode)
[neovim] dw: Delete word from cursor (normal mode)
[neovim] d$: Delete from cursor to end of line (normal mode)
[neovim] r: Replace single character (normal mode)
[neovim] u: Undo last change (normal mode)
[neovim] Ctrl+r: Redo last change (normal mode)
[neovim] .: Repeat last command (normal mode)
[neovim] /pattern: Search forward for 'pattern' (normal mode)
[neovim] ?pattern: Search backward for 'pattern' (normal mode)
[neovim] n: Next search match (normal mode)
[neovim] N: Previous search match (normal mode)
[neovim] :w: Save file (normal mode)
[neovim] :wq: Write (save) and Quit (normal mode)
[neovim] :q: Quit (if no unsaved changes) (normal mode)
[neovim] :q!: Quit without saving (normal mode)
[neovim] :e filename: Open 'filename' in current window (normal mode)
[neovim] :split: Split window horizontally (normal mode)
[neovim] :vsplit: Split window vertically (normal mode)
[neovim] Ctrl+w h/j/k/l: Navigate between splits (normal mode)
[neovim] Ctrl+w Ctrl+w: Cycle through splits (normal mode)
[neovim] Gt: Go to next tab (normal mode)
[neovim] gT: Go to previous tab (normal mode)
[neovim] :tabnew: Open new tab (normal mode)
[neovim] :tabclose: Close current tab (normal mode)
[neovim] ==: Auto-indent current line (normal mode)
[neovim] gg=G: Auto-indent entire file (normal mode)
[neovim] <C-v>: Start visual block mode (for multi-line editing) (normal mode)
# Insert Mode
[neovim] i: Enter Insert mode (at cursor) (insert mode)
[neovim] I: Enter Insert mode (at beginning of line) (insert mode)
[neovim] a: Enter Insert mode (after cursor) (insert mode)
[neovim] A: Enter Insert mode (at end of line) (insert mode)
[neovim] o: Enter Insert mode (new line below) (insert mode)
[neovim] O: Enter Insert mode (new line above) (insert mode)
[neovim] Esc: Exit Insert mode (return to Normal mode) (insert mode)
[neovim] Ctrl+[: Exit Insert mode (same as Esc) (insert mode)
# Visual Mode
[neovim] v: Enter Visual mode (character-wise selection) (visual mode)
[neovim] V: Enter Visual Line mode (line-wise selection) (visual mode)
[neovim] Ctrl+v: Enter Visual Block mode (column-wise selection) (visual mode)
[neovim] h/j/k/l: Extend selection (visual mode)
[neovim] d: Delete selected text (visual mode)
[neovim] y: Yank (copy) selected text (visual mode)
[neovim] p: Paste selected text (visual mode)
[neovim] c: Change (delete and enter Insert mode) selected text (visual mode)
[neovim] Esc: Exit Visual mode (return to Normal mode) (visual mode)
# Command-Line Mode (starting with :)
[neovim] :w: Save file (command-line mode)
[neovim] :q: Quit window/buffer (command-line mode)
[neovim] :wq: Save and quit (command-line mode)
[neovim] :e [file]: Edit a file (command-line mode)
[neovim] :s/old/new/g: Substitute 'old' with 'new' on current line (globally) (command-line mode)
[neovim] :%s/old/new/g: Substitute 'old' with 'new' throughout entire file (command-line mode)
[neovim] :%s/old/new/gc: Substitute 'old' with 'new' throughout entire file with confirmation (command-line mode)
[neovim] :tabnew [file]: Open new tab with optional file (command-line mode)
[neovim] :split [file]: Horizontal split with optional file (command-line mode)
[neovim] :vsplit [file]: Vertical split with optional file (command-line mode)
[neovim] :help [topic]: Open help for a topic (command-line mode)
[neovim] :%d: Delete all lines (command-line mode)
[neovim] :%y: Yank all lines (command-line mode)
[neovim] :set <option>: Set an option (e.g., :set nu for line numbers) (command-line mode)
[neovim] :set no<option>: Unset an option (e.g., :set nonu) (command-line mode)
